sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total volume of 51,927 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 5.2 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 112.1% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $200 strike call option expiring September 20, 2019, with 4,049 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 404,900 underlying shares of HD.
